{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, HLDA discovers hundreds of super-topics and roughly three times more sub-topics than CT.",
    "However, this approach of generating numerous small topics at all levels often leads to suboptimal results according to our evaluation metrics and an imperfect hierarchy, where a child topic is frequently present in more documents than its parent.In addition, we compare CT to nTSNTM model [15], which leverages the neural variational inference (NVI) framework and a nonparametric prior to group topics into a sensible tree structure.",
    "We utilized the publicly available code of nTSNTM 16 with the recommended parameters indicated in [15].",
    "The model was trained for 100 epochs, with a hidden size of 256, and we ensured that it was compatible with the latest version of Tensorflow in order to obtain accurate results.",
    "To maintain consistency in hardware, we executed the nTSNTM model on the same commodity hardware used by the baseline models mentioned earlier."
  ]
}